[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(8) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Above when he said.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Whereas he saith above;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or, as we might express it, “Saying at the outset,” “Setting out with saying.” In the following words the best MSS. have the plural, “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Sacrifices and offerings and whole burnt offerings and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sacrifices",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": " for sin.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The change from singular to plural is in harmony with the thought of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:1-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the repetition of sacrifices.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which are offered by the law.—Rather, such as are offered according to law. The change from “the law” to “law” seems intentional, as if the writer had in thought the contrast between any external law of ritual and a principle of inward obedience.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Which are offered by the law.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "such as are offered according to law.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " The change from “the law” to “law” seems intentional, as if the writer had in thought the contrast between any external law of ritual and a principle of inward obedience.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
